author: jm
msg: bug 5884: if a BOUNCE_MESSAGE-hitting message has no Received headers, it can still be backscatter; check to see if the bounce-generating MTA was trusted, and if not, classify as backscatter anyway, since a mail from us to an external site should always contain Received headers before it's bounced.
